{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17497034","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17497034"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T09:02:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T09:02:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1461"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1461","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1461"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.07,0.66,0.08,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1461"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101643"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1461","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1461"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1461"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84084"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1181"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"10987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26819"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33892"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42327"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44514"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45066"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101643","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/101643"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 56-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a two-week history of a painless swelling in his neck. He has no other symptoms. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. He has a 30 pack-year smoking history and drinks two cans of beer daily. He works as an accountant.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 84/min, blood pressure 122/68 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 37.2\u00b0C. His BMI is 26 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E. There is a firm, non-tender swelling in the anterior neck. The rest of the physical examination is unremarkable. A CT scan is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hodgkin lymphoma","Lipoma","Multi-nodular goitre","Carcinoma of the tongue","Carcinoma of the stomach"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe CT appearance of multiple nodules within the thyroid gland with early retrosternal extension is diagnostic of \u003Cstrong\u003Emultinodular goitre\u003C/strong\u003E. The clinical presentation of a painless anterior neck mass is characteristic. While goitre is more common in women, it can occur in men, particularly in those with risk factors such as smoking. Thyroid function tests would be required to determine if the goitre is causing any hormonal disturbance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHodgkin lymphoma\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents with painless lymph node enlargement, most commonly in the cervical region. However, lymph nodes would appear as discrete masses rather than the confluent thyroid enlargement seen here. B symptoms (fever, night sweats, weight loss) are often present, which this patient does not have.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELipoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a benign tumour of adipose tissue that would appear as a well-circumscribed, homogeneous, fat-density mass on CT. It would not typically involve the thyroid gland or show the nodular appearance seen in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarcinoma of the tongue\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents with an ulcerating lesion, pain, and cervical lymphadenopathy. The CT appearance would show a primary lesion in the tongue with possible lymph node involvement, not thyroid enlargement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarcinoma of the stomach\u003C/strong\u003E would not cause a neck mass as its primary presentation. While it can metastasise to cervical lymph nodes (Virchow\u0027s node), this would be accompanied by symptoms of gastric cancer such as weight loss, early satiety, or gastrointestinal bleeding.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Multinodular goitre typically presents as a painless neck swelling and may have retrosternal extension visible on imaging.","Risk factors for goitre include smoking, iodine deficiency, and female sex.","CT imaging is useful to assess extent of goitre and retrosternal extension."],"references":["Haynes J, Arnold KR, Aguirre-Oskins C, Hoffmann RG. Evaluation of neck masses in adults. Am Fam Physician [Internet]. 2015 May 15 [cited 2025 May 2];91(10):698\u2013706. Available from: https://www.aafp.org/pubs/afp/issues/2015/0515/p698.html"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84084"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1461"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"392"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"392","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/392"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/52f720af-65ae-41b7-901b-c29e13aedef7.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/52f720af-65ae-41b7-901b-c29e13aedef7.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":405,"height":307}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84084","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/84084"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-03T15:50:50+09:30","update